the time, it's enormous.

00:06:12.050 --> 00:06:15.620
And my feelings about
food waste and everything

00:06:15.620 --> 00:06:19.130
is things need to change
at really large scale,

00:06:19.130 --> 00:06:22.070
industrial levels
with companies,

00:06:22.070 --> 00:06:23.820
with large-scale
farms and stuff.

00:06:23.820 --> 00:06:27.920
But I think I'm also a big
believer that small differences

00:06:27.920 --> 00:06:29.220
add up to big changes.

00:06:29.220 --> 00:06:31.190
And if we as individuals
reframe the way

00:06:31.190 --> 00:06:33.590
we think about everything
we consume, whether it's

00:06:33.590 --> 00:06:36.890
food or anything, and
not throwing things out,

00:06:36.890 --> 00:06:40.850
really taking the time
to invest in good stuff--

00:06:40.850 --> 00:06:43.140
I do believe that
makes a difference.

00:06:43.140 --> 00:06:45.549
And I think that's
just a way to reframe

00:06:45.549 --> 00:06:46.590
your thinking in general.

00:06:46.590 --> 00:06:48.730
I think if you start
looking at your food-- which

00:06:48.730 --> 00:06:53.210
is the thing we consume every
day-- in this way, that's,

00:06:53.210 --> 00:06:54.530
I guess, a bit more mindful.

00:06:54.530 --> 00:06:58.670
For me, at least, it kind of
floats into everything else.

00:06:58.670 --> 00:07:00.650
